rComments: Dr. CM is incredibly knowledgeable about the content and encourages thoughtful discussion. The pop ups help you stay on top of class material and actually attend classes. She fosters critical thinking in her class, and there's a paper dedicated to developing this skill! If you don't want to use your brain to think, choose a different life path.

Dr CM is knowledgeable and kind, and she cares about her students. She does expect you to perform well to get a good grade, but for a 3rd-year class, it isn't unreasonable. Some students complain if they are used to MC tests only since she has a detailed paper and requires critical thinking short answer responses on her exams. A+ is possible!

Absolutely terrible experience. Random Pop-up reflections during the last 20 mins of class-then link close. Terrible marker. Tough is an understatement. Shocked us all with midterm grades even after adjusting the weight of questions. Heavy material. If I could give her a ZERO, I would, but that's not possible so I give her a ONE.
Professor CM is really great at what she does and shows real care for all the students in her class. Her lectures are super well made and she makes the material accessible :)

This professor is incredible! She has a great sense of humour and makes the content really accessible. I appreciate that she helps you develop your critical thinking skills. You will need to attend classes to do well. You will also need to follow instructions to do well. I wish I could take another course with her. Excellent learning experience.

Dr. Corsini-Munt is an excellent lecturer. She clearly cares about her students and the content. She has been very considerate of the fact that we are living in a pandemic. However, if you want to do well in the class, you actually need to attend. Similarly, you are required to have basic reading skills. PRO TIP: READ THE SYLLABUS AND ASSIGNMENTS.
Unclear expectations, otherwise great lecturer and seems well-intended, however fails to make clear standards and expectations for assignments.

This professor has unrealistic expectations when grading and fails to make these expectations clear for students. They say researchers don't make the best professors and she's a clear example of this. Maybe she has good intentions but she seriously needs to be lighten up. An unnecessary stressor to have during a global pandemic, avoid at all costs.
